nz.ac.auckland.morc.specification

Class OrchestratedTestSpecification

  • java.lang.Object
    • nz.ac.auckland.morc.specification.OrchestratedTestSpecification

  • public class OrchestratedTestSpecification
extends Object
    An orchestrated test is a declarative way of specifying a target for a message with a number of expectations related to call-outs required for the process that the original message triggered is deemed to be correct. A DSL builder is used to generate an instate of an orchestrated test specification which is executed as part of a MorcTest
    Author:
    David MacDonald - d.macdonald@auckland.ac.nz
